{
  "texts": [
    "Metric 2: Citation churn.",
    "As knowledge in a field evolves, some ideas receive increasing support and, eventually, may become taken-forgranted or \"blackboxed\" 47.",
    "In a healthy community, if new ideas arise that are better than the old ones, they should be recognized as such, and the old ones should be displaced.",
    "Such disruptive ideas are associated with higher novelty 48 and are predictive of the highest level of recognition in the scientific community, like the Nobel prize 49.",
    "A robust amount of turnover in reference lists across time, which we call citation churn, may thus indicate a healthy evolution of published knowledge."
  ]
}